	<p style="font-size: 24pt; margin: 24pt auto 0; text-align: center; font-weight: bold">
Spring Waltz Workshops!
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 16pt; margin: 24pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
<span style="color: red; font-weight: bold">TLDR:</span>
<a href="https://forms.gle/7Kz99wPbNFJfvaoX7">Sign up here!</a>
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 12pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
		Get excited for another round of spring waltz workshops!
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 12pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
		From the Stanford Viennese Ball Opening Committee, to you. Whether you missed taking that Social Dance I class this year, got your eye on Opening Committee auditions next fall, or just loved the dancing at Viennese Ball and want more, have we got the offering for you!		
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 20pt; margin: 24pt auto 0; text-align: center; font-weight: bold">
A Whole Bunch O' Workshops
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 4pt auto 0; text-align: center">
All workshops 8&ndash;10 PM, followed by an hour of social dancing from 10&ndash;11 PM
	</p>
	<div style="height: 1px; background: #aaa; margin: 24pt 0 0"></div>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; margin: 16pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Rotary waltz 4-week series — Wednesdays, May 10&ndash;31
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
Rotary waltz is a fast and spinny dance, a perfect dance for gliding around the dance floor! We'll teach waltz as it's danced socially today, a living tradition descended from the ballrooms of Europe. No experience required. Our goal is to take you from wherever you are to proficient and feeling awesome and confident on the dance floor.
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; color: red; font-weight: bold">
Note: this series is a 4-week commitment
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold;">
Wednesdays, 4 weeks starting May 10, 8&ndash;10 PM&nbsp; &#183; &nbsp;by Lyna & Akshay
	</p>
	<div style="height: 1px; background: #aaa; margin: 16pt 0 0"></div>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; margin: 16pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Intermediate cross-step waltz — Monday, May 22
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
Cross-step waltz is a more recent twist on the classic waltz, using a crossing step and danced to slower music. This lesson will teach intermediate variations and styling, so come prepared knowing the basics!
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; color: red; font-weight: bold">
Note: this workshop will replace Dancebreak this week
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Monday, May 22, 8&ndash;10 PM&nbsp; &#183; &nbsp;by Cyrus & Ariel
	</p>
	<div style="height: 1px; background: #aaa; margin: 16pt 0 0"></div>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; margin: 16pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Opening Committee audition prep — Tuesday, May 30
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
Got your eye on Viennese Ball Opening Committee auditions next fall? Great! We're excited to see you there. :) This workshop will teach waltz and polka skills that will help you make the most of auditions, plus give you an opportunity to ask any questions you may have. Intended for both beginner and intermediate dancers.
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; color: red; font-weight: bold">
Note: this workshop is only for Stanford students and alumni
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Tuesday, May 30, 8&ndash;10 PM&nbsp; &#183; &nbsp;by Kasey & Toby
	</p>
	<div style="height: 1px; background: #aaa; margin: 16pt 0 0"></div>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; margin: 16pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Waltz artistry — Thursday, June 1
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in">
Already know how to waltz but feel like sometimes you're just doing one variation after another? This workshop for intermediate dancers will teach you how to chain waltz variations together to bring more continuity to your dancing and create more complete musical ideas. Come prepared knowing the basics.
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; margin: 6pt auto 0; max-width: 7in; font-weight: bold">
Thursday, June 1, 8&ndash;10 PM&nbsp; &#183; &nbsp;by Jiying & Lyna
	</p>
	<div style="height: 1px; background: #aaa; margin: 16pt 0 0"></div>
	<p style="font-size: 16pt; margin: 24pt auto 0; text-align: center">
<a href="https://forms.gle/7Kz99wPbNFJfvaoX7">Sign up here!</a>
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; margin: 4pt auto 0; text-align: center">
Sign-ups are first come&ndash;first served
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; max-width: 7in; margin: 24pt auto 0">
Location
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; max-width: 7in; margin: 6pt auto 0">
Due to complexity in how Stanford now handles room bookings, we can't guarantee a location every week, and workshops may vary between dance studios in Roble, GCC Havana, Rains Hacienda Commons, EVGR C, and Elliot Program Center. Once you sign up, we'll notify you of the location for each workshop as soon as we can lock one in.
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; max-width: 7in; margin: 24pt auto 0">
		Some logistics
	</p>
	<ul style="font-size: 12pt; max-width: 7in; margin: 6pt auto 0">
		<li>No need to sign up with a partner! We'll rotate partners throughout the workshops.</li>
		<li>Socks or dance shoes only. No street shoes on the dance floor.</li>
		<li>Sign-ups are first come&ndash;first served. We'll send email confirmations once we've filled our limited spots.</li>
	</ul>
	<p style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; max-width: 7in; margin: 24pt auto 0">
Who are we?
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 12pt; max-width: 7in; margin: 6pt auto 0">
These workshops are offered by members of the Stanford Viennese Ball Opening Committee. But ultimately we're just students eager to share our love of dance!
	</p>
	<p style="font-size: 10pt; text-align: center; margin: 24pt 0 0">
We hope to see you on the dance floor!
	</p>
